meanings.english_definition: Donald Jay Fagen (born January 10, 1948) is an American musician best known as the co-founder, lead singer, and keyboardist of the rock band Steely Dan, formed in the early 1970s.

etymology.value: The surname Fagen is of Irish origin, an anglicized form of the Gaelic surname Ó Faodhagáin, meaning 'descendant of Faodhagán'. The given name Faodhagán is a double diminutive of faodh, meaning 'ornament'.
